# Billing exports (sensitive)
#
# Never commit customer billing data. The patterns below cover every
# way a real bill could land in the tree:
#   - `bills/` is the canonical scratch dir for user-supplied exports
#   - `Billing Account for*.csv` matches the default Console export name
#   - `*_billing_*.csv` / `*billing-export*` catches BigQuery export file
#     names produced by `bq extract`
# If you need to add a new safe fixture (anonymized, redistributable),
# put it under `benchmarks/real_world/` and explicitly allowlist it —
# see the FOCUS samples below.
bills/
Billing Account for*.csv
*_billing_*.csv
*billing-export*

# FOCUS Sandbox sample data (FinOps Foundation, CC BY 4.0).
# The small 738 KB file is checked in and sufficient for the skippable
# test in tests/test_focus_sandbox.py. The 7 MB and 73 MB variants are
# large enough to bloat every clone, so they stay untracked —
# contributors who want them run the curl snippet in
# benchmarks/real_world/README.md.
benchmarks/real_world/focus_sample_10000.csv
benchmarks/real_world/focus_sample_100000.csv

# Second working clone some contributors keep alongside the main
# checkout. Always untracked regardless of location.
/ghosthunter/

# Internal dev notes — never commit.
# These files contain personal/work-context that shouldn't live in a
# public repo. Claude / contributors sync state via git branches, not
# a shared CLAUDE.md.
CLAUDE.md
docs/internal/

# Claude Code local state (worktrees, local settings)
.claude/
